📌 Tactic(s)

    Reconnaissance

🧠 Description
Adversaries may gather information about the victims organization that can be used during targeting. Information about an organization may include a variety 
of details, including the names of divisions/deparments, specifics of bussines operations, as well as the roles and responsabilities of key employes.

🛠️ Real-World Examples

  Adversaries may gather information in varioues ways, such as direct elictation via Phishing for Information.
APT28 has used a large language model  (LLMs) ti gather information about satellite capabilities.

🔍 Detection Ideas

   Much of this activity may have a very high occrence and associated to false positive rate, as well as potentially taking place
outside the visibility of the target organization, making detection difficult for defenders.
🔐 Mitigation Strategies

    This technique cannot be easily mitigated with preventive controls since it is based on behaviours performed outside of the scope of enterpise defense and controls.

